DELICIOUS! My DH literally called it "da bomb," because he is stuck in 1992. I increased the Old Bay by 1/2 tsp and added some cayenne but forgot to add the lemon juice. It didn't matter. It was great anyways! Chilled for 1.5 hours, alternating freezer and fridge, then put this on a sub roll with lettuce and tomato.

Rating: 4
This was a hit with my family. I did what everyone else did and added some lemon juice and quite a lot of cayenne. Because my husband thinks it's not a real shrimp salad without avocado, I added that as well. It would also be delicious with chipotle pepper powder to give a slightly smoky flavor, perhaps grilling the shrimp beforehand.

