Rating: 3
Similar to other reviewers, I thought this recipe was a very good start, but added a few squeezes of lemon juice, a couple dashes of tabasco and substituted some leftover corn for the celery. Definitely let the salad set up in the fridge for half a day or more. I think this one is great in a lettuce leaf wrap or endives, but also does well as a sort of burrito if you add a little cilantro, wrap it up in a warm flour tortilla and lightly fry with some olive oil.

